WEBVTT

00:06.690 --> 00:10.074
God does love us and Jesus did die for us.

00:10.995 --> 00:14.759
And if you take nothing away from this service, I think that's enough.

00:16.721 --> 00:24.570
As we get going here, we are just a few days into the season of Lent for those who participate.

00:25.131 --> 00:35.282
Lent is a 40-day window in which we prepare ourselves and maybe the soil of our souls for Easter.

00:35.650 --> 00:39.840
for resurrection, for new life, for that which pops out of the ground.

00:40.682 --> 00:47.538
Over the coming weeks, you're going to hear a lot of gardening metaphors, so just get ready for that.

00:47.650 --> 00:55.178
You probably might even learn some things about how to garden your actual like physical gardens, so you're welcome in advance.

00:56.599 --> 00:58.921
I don't know a ton, everything I've learned.

00:58.941 --> 01:15.218
I've learned from Betty and Paula, and yet I will pass along a few things to you as well, because I actually think that what is happening in the physical world outside has a reflection, direct reflection,

01:15.682 --> 01:18.805
on what's happening inside of our hearts and souls.

01:19.726 --> 01:31.597
God has created this world wonderfully and within it lies the mysteries of what he's trying to do with each and every one of us.

01:32.278 --> 01:37.703
And so of the course of the next few weeks, I look forward to exploring some of this together.

01:37.743 --> 01:45.010
The sermon ahead is very quickly understood with two facts.

01:45.186 --> 01:52.454
And then one challenge, because I think that's what sermons are supposed to do at the end, is offer a challenge.

01:52.474 --> 01:58.201
Fact one, God, the great sower of seeds is showering your life with seeds.

01:59.062 --> 02:09.714
This very second, God is showering your life in this second right now, the moment you are in with his seeds.

02:09.794 --> 02:15.104
Fact number two, these seeds, however, must be received with the right kind of soil.

02:16.165 --> 02:24.921
And the challenge is that Jesus is asking you to consider what kind of soil is sitting in your heart right now.

02:25.683 --> 02:26.564
Is it compact?

02:27.366 --> 02:28.027
Is it rocky?

02:28.828 --> 02:29.489
Is it thorny?

02:30.351 --> 02:31.213
Or is it good soil?

02:32.234 --> 02:34.258
Before we begin, let us pray.

02:35.554 --> 02:39.680
Our Father in heaven, we come this morning seeking a word.

02:39.740 --> 02:52.499
The good news, Lord, is that Jesus teaches us that you are the sower of words and that you are constantly throwing those seeds out before us.

02:53.781 --> 03:00.731
And so God today, soften our hearts, soften that soil that we might hear from you.

03:01.292 --> 03:02.994
In Christ's name we pray, amen.

03:04.194 --> 03:08.340
If you'll turn with me, we'll just read the first nine verses of our passage today.

03:08.420 --> 03:10.983
It's the original parable that he tells.

03:11.844 --> 03:13.807
The whole passage goes like this.

03:13.847 --> 03:16.270
There's the parable, which is verses one through nine.

03:16.691 --> 03:34.034
There's this intermediate section in which he tells us why he talks in parables, which, if you've not thought about, is worthy of its own sermon or sermon series, maybe even, which is the fact that Jesus

03:34.370 --> 03:36.393
doesn't talk in like law.

03:36.733 --> 03:37.414
Have you noticed this?

03:37.434 --> 03:39.437
He talks in storytelling.

03:39.497 --> 03:41.520
He speaks in parables.

03:41.580 --> 03:46.326
He speaks in terms of like metaphors and analogies.

03:46.447 --> 03:55.840
Well, sometimes we might wish that he were a little more straightforward, but instead we get stories about sowers, sowing seeds, right?

03:55.900 --> 04:01.487
And this is who Jesus is and why he teaches us, but it's worth reflecting.

04:01.527 --> 04:03.410
Why would God?

04:03.970 --> 04:08.959
When God comes in the flesh, why would he speak so cryptically?

04:09.841 --> 04:11.784
Why not just be a little more straightforward?

04:12.786 --> 04:13.627
That's a different sermon.

04:14.309 --> 04:26.290
And then in the last part of the sermon, he explains the parable, which is the only time in Scripture that he gives us a reading and explanation of his parable.

04:26.370 --> 04:33.100
And so that too is worthy of your time and reflection and much of what I say is going to reflect that.

04:33.120 --> 04:38.067
But for right now, we're just gonna read again the parable itself versus one to nine.

04:39.629 --> 04:50.825
Again, he began teaching beside the sea and a very large crowd gathered about him so that he got into a boat and sat in it on the sea and the whole crowd was beside the sea on the land.

04:51.666 --> 04:54.610
And he was teaching them many things in parables

04:54.850 --> 04:58.074
And in his teaching, he said to them, listen, behold.

04:59.015 --> 05:06.905
A sewer went out to sow, and as he sowed, some seed fell along the path, and the birds came, and they devoured it.

05:07.786 --> 05:16.096
Other seed fell on rocky ground, where it did not have much soil, and immediately it sprang up, since it had no depth of soil.

05:17.037 --> 05:21.202
And when the sun rose, it was scorched, and since it had no root, it withered away.

05:21.762 --> 05:29.151
Other seed fell among thorns, and the thorns grew up and choked it, and it yielded no grain.

05:30.192 --> 05:39.664
And other seeds fell into good soil and produced grain, growing up and increasing and yielding 30-fold, 60-fold, 100-fold.

05:40.244 --> 05:44.409
And he said, he who has ears let him hear.

05:44.469 --> 05:48.274
We've got four kinds of soil, right?

05:48.875 --> 05:49.676
We've got what?

05:50.797 --> 05:51.538
The path.

05:51.970 --> 06:00.862
which is compacted, people have been walking along it, and you can imagine the seed falls onto the path, and what happens, nothing.

06:02.264 --> 06:04.247
And then there is, what's next?

06:06.029 --> 06:09.413
Bang attention, there's the rocky soil, right?

06:10.054 --> 06:15.762
Here I envision like, not just like boulders or something, but like maybe little pebbles even.

06:15.970 --> 06:32.394
Like imagine a layer of soil that's like filled with all these little pebbles in it, and it only goes so deep, and the plant tries to root down in it, but there's only so much soil to go around, and it's not enough to create a good, healthy root structure.

06:32.434 --> 06:35.218
And number three, what was the third one?

06:36.520 --> 06:37.902
The thorns, thank you, Asher.

06:39.104 --> 06:43.570
The thorns, well, this time, it seems,

06:43.874 --> 06:54.048
The crop starts to try to produce something, but the thorns choke it out, and it's not nearly as productive as it should be, if it's productive at all.

06:54.829 --> 06:56.791
And then lastly, of course, we have the good soil.

06:57.232 --> 06:58.534
And what happens with the good soil?

06:58.614 --> 07:05.343
We get 30x, 60x, 100 times of what was expected.

07:06.244 --> 07:10.210
Now you and I were aiming for the good soil.

07:10.910 --> 07:13.554
And so the question is, well, what is that?

07:13.666 --> 07:14.928
What's the good soil?

07:17.131 --> 07:17.692
We'll get there.

07:18.653 --> 07:21.758
Before we do, it's important to say a couple things.

07:22.619 --> 07:37.921
One, I find it odd that this sower, if he knows what he's doing, is putting seed in places like the path or the thorns or wherever.

07:37.981 --> 07:41.266
It'd be a little bit like, well, me,

07:41.570 --> 07:53.381
if I were trying to grow grass seed in my backyard and sometimes I have and I take handfuls of seeds and I just walk around and I just start throwing it anywhere.

07:53.421 --> 08:04.392
And suddenly it's on my patio, suddenly it's under the trees where it's not gonna grow, suddenly it's in this group of rocks that are near my shed where I don't want it to grow.

08:04.432 --> 08:10.578
Right, that is not normal for how you might seed a certain area.

08:12.034 --> 08:22.364
But this gets to a broader point, which is to say that it's not normal because me, the sower, I have limited amounts of grass seed.

08:23.926 --> 08:27.269
And if you know anything about grass seed, it's rather expensive, actually.

08:28.110 --> 08:29.191
And so you don't want to waste it.

08:29.751 --> 08:30.892
You don't want to just throw it anywhere.

08:31.453 --> 08:32.614
You want to be very specific.

08:34.075 --> 08:38.540
But God, the great sower, God has endless seeds.

08:39.601 --> 08:40.882
His word,

08:41.154 --> 08:47.262
is endless, and he is willing to throw it out all the time and at any moment.

08:48.323 --> 08:58.537
And so what you need to know is that God is throwing seeds in great abundance into your life at any and all points.

08:59.198 --> 09:08.530
And it doesn't matter if it's rocky, it doesn't matter if you're on the path, it doesn't matter if it's good or soil or thorny, whatever it is.

09:08.802 --> 09:12.187
God is throwing seeds.

09:12.207 --> 09:28.130
In hopes that you are amending the soil of your life, that you might be able to receive it and hear what God is doing in you and through you, for you, with you.

09:28.150 --> 09:36.722
As we've already said, there are four soils, but there is just one field

09:36.962 --> 09:42.471
And I actually think that in some ways, this is representative of all of us.

09:42.491 --> 09:43.593
There's just one me.

09:44.194 --> 09:51.166
But I certainly have within me various parts of my life that represent each of these.

09:51.326 --> 09:52.608
All four of these.

09:52.668 --> 10:03.346
The hope, of course, is that my good soil is a much larger patch than the rocky or the thorny.

10:03.682 --> 10:08.109
Truth be told, like, the garden of my life is vast.

10:09.151 --> 10:11.214
And there are parts of it that need tending.

10:11.254 --> 10:13.438
And some of it is rocky.

10:14.079 --> 10:17.123
And it's time to get in there and to do some work.

10:17.664 --> 10:31.346
And so over the course of the next four weeks, we're actually going to stick with this one parable, or at least the ideas behind it, and then ask ourselves, what would rocky soil look like in real life, like in your real life?

10:32.098 --> 10:35.582
And if it's in there, how do I get that out?

10:36.043 --> 10:40.007
How do I dig around enough to change that kind of soil?

10:40.027 --> 10:59.090
And then in the fourth week, we'll talk about what it means to have healthy soil, and to have that really dark, rich, nutrient-filled soil that's capable of growing the kind of thing that God is trying to grow in our lives.

11:01.442 --> 11:15.899
There's another fact about this nice parable and nice metaphor that God has given us in the parable, which is that while it might seem like the soil of your life just is your life, right?

11:16.200 --> 11:22.387
That the path is just always the path and that the rocky soil is just always the rocky.

11:22.427 --> 11:28.114
If you're a gardener in the room, you know that's not necessarily true.

11:28.418 --> 11:39.417
There are ways to amend your soil, to actually change it so that it is conducive to God's work in your life.

11:40.939 --> 11:43.764
We've been talking a lot about transformation around here.

11:43.804 --> 11:48.272
There's a reason you can change.

11:49.734 --> 11:54.322
Your life as it is right now is not your destiny.

11:55.874 --> 12:01.781
You can be a different person in six months, a year, 10 years from now.

12:02.582 --> 12:10.131
God can and wants to do a work in each and every one of you, every last one of you.

12:11.673 --> 12:22.546
And the question is, will I do the work internally amend the soil of my soul so that God is able to do that work in there?

12:25.666 --> 12:37.972
As I've already said, Betty and Paula have taught me a few things already about the way soil works and gardening works.

12:38.974 --> 12:42.642
And there's just two right now I kind of want to give to you.

12:42.763 --> 12:46.290
One is it requires like actual labor.

12:47.010 --> 12:49.694
It doesn't just happen of its own accord.

12:49.814 --> 12:59.066
In order to be somebody who amends their garden, the soil, you got to dig down in and you got to get the dirt under the fingernails.

12:59.126 --> 13:01.990
And you got to actually do the work, right?

13:02.030 --> 13:11.442
Paula taught me that every year she and art, they go to the Lorton dump.

13:11.810 --> 13:24.366
and he backs up and they dump a bunch of leaf mulch, old leaf mulch into the truck and then they drive it to her house and then they lay that leaf mulch everywhere.

13:24.567 --> 13:25.107
And why?

13:25.127 --> 13:32.417
Well, because it's filled with the nutrients and it takes a lot of work and they're putting it all over the yard.

13:32.957 --> 13:36.562
But if you've ever been to her house and you've seen her yard,

13:36.834 --> 13:49.869
If you were like dig down, I mean, it's some of the most nutrient-rich soil that's probably in existence in Northern Virginia, because every year, she just puts this stuff in her grass, right?

13:50.069 --> 13:52.632
And it's not actually in her plants, it's everywhere.

13:55.035 --> 13:58.860
And you wonder, like, well, how does she get her health so beautiful?

13:59.160 --> 14:01.102
How does she make her yard look so nice?

14:02.043 --> 14:04.466
It's not by accident.

14:04.802 --> 14:06.845
There's intention behind it.

14:07.226 --> 14:08.168
It takes work.

14:09.710 --> 14:11.473
She lays the nutrients down.

14:12.234 --> 14:13.256
She feeds it.

14:14.518 --> 14:21.970
But then the second part is maybe of equal importance, and it's an expectation setting.

14:21.990 --> 14:29.202
I can't remember who it was that taught me this, but that when you plant something,

14:29.346 --> 14:35.031
It takes actually like three or so years to really start doing what it's supposed to be doing.

14:35.051 --> 14:47.463
And the phrase goes like this, in the first year it sleeps, the second year it creeps, the third year it leaps, sleep, creep, and then leap, right?

14:47.483 --> 14:48.264
Has anyone heard this?

14:48.644 --> 14:49.265
Who knows this?

14:49.605 --> 14:49.766
Yeah.

14:50.766 --> 14:58.674
So this is not all that different from how transformation works in your actual life.

14:59.522 --> 15:21.612
Like if you want to be somebody who is changed, my guess is all of that hard work of like laying down the nutrient-rich soil, like that in year one is going to take a ton of work and you're probably not going to see the immediate result of it like that year because the plant of your soul is going to sleep.

15:22.674 --> 15:26.259
It's going to take time to get the roots really dug down deep.

15:27.020 --> 15:28.722
And so my encouragement would be

15:30.434 --> 15:31.635
Take the time it takes.

15:32.737 --> 15:33.938
Don't give up too soon.

15:34.799 --> 15:36.020
Keep the digging.

15:36.701 --> 15:39.625
Because then in the second year, it starts to creep.

15:40.526 --> 15:44.270
And you start to realize, oh, things are a little different.

15:44.951 --> 15:45.872
Things are changing.

15:46.613 --> 15:49.897
I'm noticing the growth that I just didn't notice before.

15:49.917 --> 15:55.043
And then in the third year, then you see the leap, right?

15:55.843 --> 15:58.066
And you realize, oh, whoa.

15:58.210 --> 16:01.475
Something is actually really different here.

16:01.535 --> 16:06.363
That's at least the way the natural world works.

16:07.665 --> 16:08.646
But what works in here?

16:09.167 --> 16:11.190
Well, I actually think it's kind of similar.

16:11.911 --> 16:17.200
It takes a while to really change, to become someone new.

16:17.220 --> 16:22.408
Sometimes, I will say, sometimes it happens overnight.

16:22.808 --> 16:25.553
And there are those experiences that change you forever.

16:25.593 --> 16:26.514
That's real.

16:26.818 --> 16:47.602
Like these things do happen, but the kind of change we're talking about here, sanctification, transformation, these things take, I've always said like a lifetime, but the work that you're doing, it might even take three years, two years, one year, to take the time it takes.

16:52.354 --> 16:57.540
It is important to say, lest you misunderstand what we're talking about here.

16:57.600 --> 17:11.377
It can seem like the work that's being done in your life is your work, that you are the one affecting change.

17:12.358 --> 17:21.970
And so maybe just one step back, offering you a very brief theology of what's really happening in your transformation.

17:22.402 --> 17:23.444
It looks like this.

17:24.265 --> 17:26.048
It's grace all the way down.

17:27.049 --> 17:27.410
Grace.

17:28.311 --> 17:33.359
It is God who is throwing those seeds out, whether you receive them or not.

17:33.939 --> 17:35.101
That is God's grace.

17:36.824 --> 17:42.052
It is God's grace that grows the plants within your soil.

17:42.252 --> 17:44.055
You don't do that, right?

17:44.876 --> 17:48.962
It is God's grace that turns the growth into actual fruit.

17:49.723 --> 17:51.506
You don't do that either.

17:52.098 --> 17:53.520
So what do you do?

17:53.540 --> 17:57.266
Your job is maybe simplest yet.

17:58.468 --> 18:11.107
You simply receive it with a willing heart, with a heart that has the right amended soil, that you open yourself to the work that God is trying to do in your life.

18:12.069 --> 18:14.172
That, that is your work.

18:15.113 --> 18:20.882
And then you allow God to do the work that God wants to do in your life.

18:21.890 --> 18:26.655
It is grace all the way down, but your work is not just passive.

18:27.136 --> 18:29.579
You're not just sitting there waiting for this to happen.

18:29.639 --> 18:34.144
Your role is to tend the soil of your soul.

18:37.367 --> 18:50.482
As I was preparing for this sermon, I thought, well, I should probably give some kind of nice story to illustrate how this works and what this looks like.

18:51.426 --> 18:58.275
And then I thought, well, maybe I'll give a story about some famous person or maybe somebody that I knew.

18:58.295 --> 19:11.031
And the more I sat with it, the more I thought it is important that I tell you something real, something that I know from my personal experience, something that is me.

19:12.993 --> 19:19.922
So forgive me for a moment, but I do want to share with you like something very real

19:20.418 --> 19:27.326
and a time in my life where transformation was both necessary and where it began to occur.

19:28.808 --> 19:39.161
You've heard some of me, some of you have heard me talk about my years in Alabama and then the transition here into Northern Virginia.

19:39.221 --> 19:46.610
And I don't want to go too far down that road because some of you have heard it too many times and you might be tired of it.

19:48.131 --> 19:50.354
But I do want to offer you this

19:50.434 --> 19:53.479
story from the perspective of transformation.

19:53.499 --> 20:05.177
2016 was the year, and it has to be one of the most important years of my life because I look back on it as this hinge point in my own life's journey.

20:06.579 --> 20:08.241
We were living in small town Alabama.

20:09.784 --> 20:11.086
For perspective, I was 37.

20:11.286 --> 20:16.434
I had three kids, ages eight, five, and Asher was a newborn.

20:17.570 --> 20:21.716
I was working at least 60 hours a week at the college that I was teaching at.

20:22.397 --> 20:27.824
And then on the weekends and midweek, I was preaching and teaching at Uniontown Baptist Church.

20:29.326 --> 20:32.731
I was probably averaging four and a half to six hours of sleep at night.

20:34.273 --> 20:36.196
We were isolated in a very small town.

20:37.157 --> 20:40.062
We had no friends because they had either moved away or died.

20:40.102 --> 20:46.130
And if you know me, you know that I have a seizure disorder.

20:46.562 --> 20:58.455
And I have it under control most of the time, but by the end of those years, I was having one every other month, and it was becoming a real problem because of the stress of my life.

21:00.237 --> 21:06.144
And I got to this point where my life was more or less felt like at a breaking point.

21:07.425 --> 21:15.474
I had worked incredibly hard to build the life that I was living, but it felt like I was about to collapse under the weight of it all.

21:16.418 --> 21:20.023
And my marriage was failing on top of all that.

21:21.165 --> 21:25.051
The soil of my life in this time, what was it like?

21:26.674 --> 21:27.555
It was certainly dry.

21:27.595 --> 21:29.678
It was parched.

21:30.820 --> 21:36.088
It was compacted like the path that Jesus describes in the parable.

21:38.111 --> 21:45.362
From my vantage point now, looking back 10 years, I can say that

21:45.730 --> 21:52.940
I'm certain that God was raining down seeds on the soil, that compacted soil of my life.

21:54.602 --> 21:58.667
But in that moment of time, it did not feel that way.

22:00.169 --> 22:01.331
It did not feel that way at all.

22:02.472 --> 22:03.053
And why?

22:03.073 --> 22:12.786
Well, because it was bouncing off the hardness of the soil of my life and the birds were coming and just eating it up,

22:13.378 --> 22:15.801
And the wind was just sweeping it away.

22:15.861 --> 22:20.707
And as much as I actually did want to hear from God, I did.

22:20.747 --> 22:21.908
I desperately did.

22:21.988 --> 22:22.549
I needed it.

22:22.569 --> 22:29.557
The circumstances of my life, well, they had me in a very dry period.

22:31.099 --> 22:33.662
So what happened next was grace upon grace.

22:34.643 --> 22:36.946
I've already said that it's grace all the way down.

22:37.006 --> 22:40.690
And so God is trying to reach out to me.

22:41.090 --> 22:46.415
And he manages to, as some of you know, through a gift that Kendall gave to me.

22:46.435 --> 22:51.900
The gift was simply sending me to a monastery for four days, where it was just me.

22:52.501 --> 22:53.402
It was silence.

22:53.922 --> 22:56.344
And I was able to just simply be.

22:56.404 --> 22:59.527
And I was asking some really tough questions of God.

23:00.248 --> 23:03.952
And I was journaling through that window of time.

23:04.672 --> 23:10.738
And I realize now that the journals from those four days

23:10.882 --> 23:18.351
perhaps the most important, one of the most important items that I own in life.

23:20.014 --> 23:30.967
Because in that journal, I wrote down what I believed God was revealing to me in this moment, the ways in which God was trying to reach out to me.

23:31.028 --> 23:36.114
And so I walked away with these six revelations.

23:36.418 --> 23:37.079
That's what I wrote.

23:37.559 --> 23:40.303
Revelation 1, they literally say, Revelation 1.

23:40.343 --> 23:42.245
And then I kind of write in Revelation 2.

23:43.126 --> 23:50.195
And I believed and to this day still believe that they were and that it was God like literally saying, you need to do these things.

23:51.436 --> 23:52.197
But here's the thing.

23:52.818 --> 24:05.874
When I look back on those revelations, they would maybe be surprising to most of you because they weren't spiritual, mostly spiritual in nature.

24:06.818 --> 24:08.300
They're actually very physical.

24:09.000 --> 24:10.282
They're very bodily.

24:11.443 --> 24:14.006
They had everything to do with my sleep.

24:15.227 --> 24:16.429
How much sleep I was getting.

24:16.949 --> 24:18.491
They had everything to do with my routines.

24:19.973 --> 24:23.136
What I was doing in the evenings and the mornings.

24:24.317 --> 24:26.460
How much time I was spending with my family.

24:26.520 --> 24:28.302
How much time I was spending alone.

24:29.083 --> 24:31.986
What I was doing with my days and my hours.

24:34.210 --> 24:44.063
This week or a couple weeks ago, rather, I came across a book called The Body Teaches the Soul by a guy named Justin Early.

24:44.263 --> 24:45.345
I recommend this to you.

24:45.886 --> 24:53.716
But I hate that this guy wrote this book because as I'm reading it, I'm thinking I should have written this book.

24:54.497 --> 25:00.625
This is a book that is needed to be written for centuries, maybe.

25:01.927 --> 25:04.050
And in some ways, the premise is quite simple.

25:04.962 --> 25:10.108
It's that we often get things, well, it's not even upside down.

25:10.769 --> 25:22.984
We just don't realize that the transformation goes both ways, which is to say we think that the transformation happens with some sort of spiritual or mental thing that happens with our lives.

25:23.064 --> 25:25.608
And then that changes everything else.

25:26.308 --> 25:26.809
And that's true.

25:27.029 --> 25:29.232
It can and does sometimes.

25:30.634 --> 25:34.098
But his point and what I would also want to say to you

25:34.850 --> 25:42.618
is that the bodily life that we live, it too actually transforms the other direction.

25:44.541 --> 25:54.011
And so he has chapters on like breathing, eating, drinking, sleeping, sickness and pain.

25:54.832 --> 25:58.496
And his point there is maybe one that a lot of you can resonate with.

25:59.056 --> 26:04.402
If you're in sickness or you're in pain and you're trying to be a spiritual person,

26:05.058 --> 26:07.301
We'll just forget about it.

26:07.321 --> 26:18.635
You suddenly realize you've come to your wits end and you're incapable of being the kind of spiritual person you want to be because your body is racked with pain.

26:22.539 --> 26:31.250
If you're sleeping four and a half hours a night like I was in Alabama and you're expecting to hear from God, forget about it.

26:33.954 --> 26:45.971
I think a lot of our spiritual growth is happening downstream from making sure that our bodies are actually taken care of.

26:47.012 --> 26:53.901
And this is exactly what we find in, well, this book teaches that the body teaches the soul.

26:55.504 --> 26:57.847
And so he talks a lot about exercise.

26:57.907 --> 27:00.951
He even talks about sex if you need a reason to buy the book.

27:01.933 --> 27:02.994
Technology.

27:03.138 --> 27:06.301
and how it affects our spirits and our souls.

27:08.284 --> 27:21.838
It took me personally getting to the point where I felt like my life was about to fall apart, like I was a speeding train about to fly off the tracks, to finally wake up and say, I need a change.

27:22.819 --> 27:24.341
Something has to break.

27:25.262 --> 27:27.244
It's time to get radical.

27:28.846 --> 27:32.530
That was the beginning of a real change in my life.

27:33.122 --> 27:38.992
a path toward abundance, but please do not misunderstand me.

27:40.054 --> 27:43.019
Growth didn't immediately happen.

27:44.481 --> 27:50.792
First, remember, it slept, sleep, and then it began to creep, and then it began to leap.

27:52.014 --> 27:56.722
But it takes a while and take the time that it takes.

27:59.266 --> 28:03.050
In closing, I would encourage you to find your why.

28:03.070 --> 28:05.733
I think I've said this before, but maybe I haven't.

28:07.094 --> 28:21.469
Find your why, because real change in your life requires motivation, some kind of motivating force that gets you out of your seat and actually says, all right, I'm gonna really do something this time.

28:21.509 --> 28:26.514
In Alabama, for me, it was a burning platform

28:27.234 --> 28:32.142
My life felt like at least it was falling apart and I needed to do something different.

28:33.183 --> 28:34.445
I needed to get radical.

28:35.347 --> 28:36.128
It was urgent.

28:36.208 --> 28:37.089
It was pressing.

28:37.149 --> 28:39.173
And so I had a why.

28:39.193 --> 28:43.119
I knew exactly why I needed to do something different.

28:44.501 --> 28:47.666
Then you might not be in that position, but you might be.

28:47.986 --> 28:52.994
Maybe you've already got your why and it is loud and clear and it's time to do something about it.

28:54.296 --> 28:55.538
But if you need a why,

28:56.450 --> 28:57.372
Let me offer a few.

28:58.835 --> 28:59.858
Maybe it's your kids.

29:02.764 --> 29:10.541
The greatest gift that you can give your children is the healthiest you possible.

29:12.225 --> 29:16.274
You can only give them of what you have.

29:17.538 --> 29:28.474
And so if you are dry and parched and that path is beaten down or it's the the rocky soil and you're trying to give out of that, well, good luck.

29:30.637 --> 29:41.173
The best thing that you can do for your kids is to have healthy soil, to have an abundant life and to give out of that.

29:42.796 --> 29:47.122
Maybe it's your spouse, maybe a year ago or

29:47.266 --> 30:06.608
five years ago or 50 years ago, you said, I do, and you made promises in front of a crowd of people, and you intend to keep those promises, and you want to love your spouse in sickness and in health, and you want to give your life away for them.

30:06.648 --> 30:15.058
The best thing that you can do is to amend the soil of your life, to soften your heart,

30:15.394 --> 30:20.680
to allow God to do some work in there and to start growing some things in abundance.

30:21.481 --> 30:27.467
So that you have 30 times, 60 times, 100 times the abundance that you used to.

30:27.487 --> 30:34.255
And now, now you can start feeding some people with that, including and especially your spouse.

30:36.237 --> 30:37.318
Or maybe you're not married.

30:38.339 --> 30:41.382
Maybe you're younger and you're just starting out in life.

30:42.303 --> 30:44.626
And you're thinking to yourself, what's my why?

30:45.378 --> 30:46.279
What's my why?

30:49.424 --> 31:07.192
There is a version of you 10 years from now and 30 years from now, maybe even 70 years from now, chances on your life and you're thinking to yourself, I had chances to become what I needed to become.

31:08.334 --> 31:13.842
Right now is an opportunity to say, I wanna amend the soil of my soul

31:14.530 --> 31:17.674
I want to start putting nutrients into my soul.

31:18.455 --> 31:24.663
I want to focus on the right things because I want to become a man or a woman of God.

31:26.405 --> 31:34.436
Somebody who is feeding the masses with the abundance that he is doing in my soul.

31:35.737 --> 31:40.043
That is a reason to wake up every morning and to do the right thing.

31:40.243 --> 31:42.386
That is a why to live with.

31:48.642 --> 31:49.102
fact.

31:51.225 --> 32:00.094
God is the great sower of seeds and he is showering your life with seeds this very moment.

32:01.415 --> 32:09.203
Fact, these seeds must be received with the right kind of soil and the challenge.

32:10.304 --> 32:14.008
What kind of soil is in your heart right now?

32:15.470 --> 32:15.890
Let's pray.

32:24.674 --> 32:25.014
father.

32:32.622 --> 32:54.162
We look around outside and though it is cold and we are all expecting a little snow today, we know that in just a few weeks, just a few weeks, there will be growth poking out of the ground and there will be new leaves

32:54.754 --> 32:56.756
on the trees that look dead right now.

32:59.359 --> 33:08.690
And the sun will be shining a little brighter and the temperatures will be warmer and the world will be coming back to life.

33:10.993 --> 33:13.976
God now is the time to make decisions.

33:15.538 --> 33:17.661
Decisions about the life we intend to lead.

33:17.701 --> 33:22.226
Decisions about the soil sitting in our souls.

33:23.138 --> 33:33.930
Soil that is either compacted, rocky, thorny, or by God's grace is good soil.

33:33.950 --> 33:38.075
God, may we be people who choose the good.

33:39.336 --> 33:45.223
May we nourish our souls with the nourishment that you give us.

33:46.505 --> 33:51.250
May we amend that soil so that we might live lives

33:51.618 --> 33:57.924
that are producing an abundant crop that only you are capable of producing.

33:57.944 --> 34:00.887
You have put us here, each and every one of us.

34:00.927 --> 34:05.112
You have put us here to feed the masses.

34:05.132 --> 34:06.813
None of us are average people.

34:07.654 --> 34:10.837
All of us have purpose.

34:10.857 --> 34:16.623
All of us have been placed on this earth with tasks to do.

34:16.643 --> 34:19.346
God, you have empowered us to do that task.

34:20.130 --> 34:33.701
May we not shrink back from it, but may we be bold and step out in faith and be the kinds of people who live big lives for you, for your kingdom.

34:36.708 --> 34:39.154
God, we pray all of this, Christ's Holy Spirit.

